\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {A.55}{\ignorespaces Blind regime, random ISI per trial, no pilots. CMA-blind and MLP-169 converge to near-identical BER by 20\,dB (0.0024 vs.\ 0.0024). Viterbi-blind's decision-directed channel bootstrap is visibly less stable than the other two: its 95\% confidence interval at 10\,dB is roughly 9$\times $ wider than the MLP's (\(\pm 0.088\) vs.\ \(\pm 0.010\)), reflecting occasional bootstrap-estimate failures on individual trials rather than a difference in mean performance.}}{120}{figure.caption.144}\protected@file@percent }
