\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {A.56}{\ignorespaces (a) Viterbi payload BER vs.\ pilot count at 10\,dB: performance is flat and below the zero-pilot MLP/CMA references down to 10 pilots, then collapses sharply at 5 pilots (0.119) -- consistent with an identifiability floor when too few pilot symbols remain to resolve the channel's degrees of freedom. (b) Block-length sweep with a fixed 10-pilot preamble: pilot overhead falls from 25\% (L=40) to 1\% (L=1000) as block length grows, while the MLP relay carries zero pilot overhead throughout.}}{121}{figure.caption.145}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:supp-partial}{{A.56}{121}{(a) Viterbi payload BER vs.\ pilot count at 10\,dB: performance is flat and below the zero-pilot MLP/CMA references down to 10 pilots, then collapses sharply at 5 pilots (0.119) -- consistent with an identifiability floor when too few pilot symbols remain to resolve the channel's degrees of freedom. (b) Block-length sweep with a fixed 10-pilot preamble: pilot overhead falls from 25\% (L=40) to 1\% (L=1000) as block length grows, while the MLP relay carries zero pilot overhead throughout}{figure.caption.145}{}}
\newlabel{fig:supp-partial@cref}{{[figure][56][2147483647,1]A.56}{[1][120][]121}}
